  "text": "Mutations that disrupt conserved tertiary interactions in the ribozyme were introduced into pAZ-IVS by QuikChange (Stratagene) or by PCR amplification of transcription templates. Mutation sites were selected based on crystal structures (Adams et al., 2004b) , Nucleotide Analog Interference Mapping (NAIM) [CITATION_1] , and other biochemical studies [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . See Table  S1 for details.",
